## DAILY RESET CONTEXT
# Pluralsight sandbox WIPES every night. The learner's AWS account has zero
# resources at 09:00 every morning. EVERY Lambda, queue, table, stream, role,
# state machine, endpoint, dashboard, alarm, monitor must be recreated daily.
#
# Implication for Cascade:
# - NEVER assume a resource exists. Always verify (describe-* / get-* / list-*)
#   before referencing.
# - Idempotent code only — every infra mutation must be "create-or-update".
# - Resolve ALL IDs at runtime: account ID via `aws sts get-caller-identity`,
#   queue URLs via `aws sqs get-queue-url`, role ARNs via `aws iam get-role`.
#   NEVER hard-code account numbers, ARNs, queue URLs.
# - Learner runs `bash scripts/bootstrap_day10.sh <learner>` at start of day
#   (or invokes `/day10-bootstrap` Cascade workflow). This brings up everything
#   Days 1-9 created, plus the SageMaker endpoint, plus Day-10 prep.
# - If Cascade is asked to "deploy X", first check if X exists. If yes, update.
#   If no, create. NEVER skip the check.
# - At end of day, learner runs `bash scripts/bootstrap_day10.sh <learner> --teardown`
#   to free shared caps (especially the SageMaker endpoint cap).

## KNOWN-ERROR REGISTER (Day-10 sandbox quirks)
# Cascade: if you see any of these errors verbatim, apply the noted fix WITHOUT
# asking the user. These are sandbox-API quirks discovered the hard way; the
# fix is mechanical.
#
# 1. `Limit exceeded on dimensional spend monitor creation` (Cost Explorer)
#    Cause: 1 DIMENSIONAL monitor per account.
#    Fix:   Look up `Default-Services-Monitor`, reuse its ARN.
#
# 2. `Unknown parameter in Metrics[N]: "Offset"` (CloudWatch put-metric-alarm)
#    Cause: `Offset` is console-only; API rejects it.
#    Fix:   Use `ANOMALY_DETECTION_BAND(m_curr, 2)` with `ThresholdMetricId`
#           and `LessThanLowerOrGreaterThanUpperThreshold` instead of a
#           hand-rolled m_prev/m_curr math expression.
#
# 3. `Should NOT have more than 4 items` (CloudWatch put-dashboard)
#    Cause: A metric tuple's math-expression object has > 4 keys, OR a metric
#           tuple has a nested `metric: [...]` field (also rejected).
#    Fix:   Use flat tuples `[Namespace, MetricName, DimName, DimValue, {opts}]`
#           with at most `{expression, label, id, color}` in math objects.
#
# 4. `Daily or weekly frequencies only support Email subscriptions` (CE subscription)
#    Cause: SNS subscribers require `Frequency: IMMEDIATE`.
#    Fix:   Use IMMEDIATE; DAILY/WEEKLY are email-only.
#
# 5. `ResourceLimitExceeded` on `create-endpoint` (SageMaker)
#    Cause: 1-endpoint-per-account cap; another learner has it.
#    Fix:   Either wait for it to free, OR run bootstrap with `--skip-endpoint`
#           and proceed without predict Lambda functioning. Dashboard tolerates.
#
# 6. `Lambda accelya-dlq-replayer-<learner> → MISSING` (Day-10 pre-flight)
#    Cause: Day-5 starter-repo handler was never deployed before Day 10.
#    Fix:   bootstrap_day10.sh STAGE 7 deploys it. If the script is older,
#           run `bash trainer-deliverables/52_deploy_dlq_replayer.sh <learner>`.
#
# 7. `cannot publish to SNS topic` (Cost Anomaly Detection)
#    Cause: SNS topic policy doesn't allow `costalerts.amazonaws.com` to publish.
#    Fix:   Patch the SNS topic Policy attribute with a statement allowing
#           Principal.Service=costalerts.amazonaws.com on sns:Publish.
#
# 8. `NumberOfPolicyVersions limit exceeded` (IAM)
#    Cause: 5-version cap on customer-managed policy.
#    Fix:   Prune oldest non-default version, THEN create-policy-version.
#
# 9. IAM eventual consistency (any "permission denied" right after a role
#    change or policy update)
#    Cause: IAM updates propagate over 10-30s globally.
#    Fix:   `sleep 15` after IAM mutations, then retry the failing operation.

