## OBSERVABILITY CONTEXT
# Use this block when Cascade scaffolds ANY Lambda or modifies the ASL.
# Applies from Day 10 forward. Three pillars + cost as 4th unofficial pillar.

- powertools versions (PIN — do NOT upgrade without trainer approval):
    aws-lambda-powertools[tracer]==2.43.1
- Required helpers (ALWAYS via src/common/observability.py — NEVER hand-roll):
    from common.observability import (
        get_logger, get_metrics, get_tracer,
        get_correlation_id, flush_metrics_early,
    )

- Correlation ID contract (MANDATORY chain — use get_correlation_id helper):
    Precedence:
      1. envelope['correlation_id']
      2. envelope.get('envelope', {}).get('correlation_id')
      3. envelope.get('event_id')                 # Day-7 PK
      4. f'corr-{uuid4()}'                        # fresh fallback
    NEVER call uuid.uuid4() inside the handler — use the helper.

- powertools Logger contract:
    @logger.inject_lambda_context(correlation_id_path='correlation_id', log_event=False)
    def handler(event, context): ...
    # log_event=False to avoid PII leakage; logs the structured fields you add explicitly.

- EMF metric namespace: Accelya/Pipeline
- EMF service dimension: powertools auto-adds 'service' from Metrics(service=...)
- EMF dimensions (max 3 per metric — CW cost spikes after that):
    auto:        service
    common:      model_version (when present), source_system (when present)
- Per-Lambda standard metrics (every handler emits at least these):
    RecordsOk         Count          (records successfully processed)
    RecordsErr        Count          (records failed)
    Duration          Milliseconds   (handler wall-clock)
- Per-component additional metrics:
    bedrock_enrich:    InputTokenCount, OutputTokenCount, CostPerRecordEstimate
    predict:           ModelLatency, ColdStart (0|1), CostPerRecordEstimate, HourlyConfidenceMean
    consumer:          KinesisRecordsClaimed, SFNStartExecutionLatency
    persist_enriched:  EnrichedBytesWritten, EnrichedRecordsWritten
- Flush-early rule (timeout-risk paths — MANDATORY):
    metrics.flush_metrics()  BEFORE invoke_endpoint()
    metrics.flush_metrics()  BEFORE bedrock-runtime.invoke_model()
    Reason: Lambda hard-timeout kills the decorator's exit emit → metric lost.

- X-Ray tracing — all 10 Lambdas + state machine:
    Lambda TracingConfig:  Mode=Active   (set via update-function-configuration)
    Tracer decorator:      @tracer.capture_lambda_handler
    State machine:         tracingConfiguration={enabled:true}
- X-Ray trace header propagation MANDATORY:
    consumer/handler.py BEFORE sfn.start_execution:
        trace_header = os.environ.get('_X_AMZN_TRACE_ID')
    sfn.start_execution(
        stateMachineArn=...,
        name=f'enrich-{correlation_id}',
        input=...,
        traceHeader=trace_header,            # ← non-optional from D10 onward
    )

- CloudWatch Logs:
    Retention: 14 days on every /aws/lambda/accelya-* log group
    Set via: aws logs put-retention-policy --retention-in-days 14
    NEVER leave a log group at 'Never Expire' in production code.

- Alarm thresholds (when authoring infra/alarms-*.json):
    iterator-age-<learner>:
        Metric:         GetRecords.IteratorAgeMilliseconds (AWS/Kinesis)
        Stat:           Maximum
        Period:         60s
        Eval/Datapts:   5 / 5
        Threshold:      60000  (60s — 1 batch behind)
        TreatMissing:   notBreaching
    bedrock-throttle-<learner>:
        Metric:         InvocationThrottles (AWS/Bedrock)
        Dimension:      ModelId
        Stat:           Sum
        Period:         300s
        Eval/Datapts:   1 / 1
        Threshold:      5
    confidence-drift-<learner>:
        Form:           ANOMALY_DETECTION_BAND (2-sigma)
        Metrics:
            m_curr  = HourlyConfidenceMean (Accelya/Pipeline) period=3600 Avg
            ad1     = ANOMALY_DETECTION_BAND(m_curr, 2)
        ThresholdMetricId: ad1
        ComparisonOp:   LessThanLowerOrGreaterThanUpperThreshold
        Eval/Datapts:   1 / 1 hr
        TreatMissing:   notBreaching
        NOTE: A hand-rolled "compare to prior hour" math expression is NOT
        supported by put-metric-alarm — the `Offset` parameter exists only
        in the CW console, not the API (Unknown parameter in Metrics[N]:
        Offset). ANOMALY_DETECTION_BAND is the supported equivalent and
        auto-baselines + implicitly count-guards.

- Cost monitor (NOT a CW alarm — different surface):
    Service:    AWS Cost Anomaly Detection
    Region:     us-east-1 (global service)
    Scope:      tag programme=accelya
    Threshold:  $10
    Lag:        8-24h (acceptable; not real-time)
    Subscribe:  SNS topic accelya-alarms-<learner> in ap-south-1 (cross-region OK)

- Cost-per-record EMF formula (CostPerRecordEstimate metric):
    bedrock_cost = (input_tokens + output_tokens) × 0.003 / 1000
    lambda_cost  = (duration_ms / 1000) × (memory_mb / 1024) × 0.0000166667
    total        = bedrock_cost + lambda_cost
    Emit on bedrock_enrich AND predict handlers.

- Tagging contract (every AWS resource):
    programme=accelya
    owner=<learner>
    environment=lab
    NB: tagging CLI syntax differs by service — see helper:
        scripts/tag_module10_resources.sh

- Sampling rule (X-Ray, lab override):
    Rule name:     accelya-lab-trace-all-<learner>
    FixedRate:     1.0  (trace 100% during lab)
    Priority:      1
    Reservoir:     1
    Cleanup:       MUST delete at end of Lab 1 — back to Default (5%)

- Forbidden patterns:
    - boto3 cloudwatch.put_metric_data() in hot path  (use EMF via powertools)
    - Generating new uuid for correlation_id outside producer
    - Skipping traceHeader= on sfn.start_execution
    - Leaving log groups at 'Never Expire'
    - Wildcard Resource in IAM policy after Lab 3
    - Wildcard Action on write/modify verbs
    - put_metric_data calls inside per-record loops
    - Manual `logging.getLogger('app')` — use get_logger() helper

- IAM tightening (post Lab 3):
    accelya-pipeline-policy version-5 cap:
        Before create-policy-version, capture PREV; prune oldest if at 5/5.
    IAM eventual consistency:
        sleep 15 after set-as-default before canary.
    Auto-rollback rule:
        Canary execution must reach SUCCEEDED within 60s
        OR set-default-policy-version back to PREV.

- Access Analyzer gate split (CI integration in Day 11):
    ERROR or SECURITY_WARNING → BLOCK (exit 1; MR cannot merge)
    GENERAL_WARNING or SUGGESTION → COMMIT findings to MR for human review
    NEVER auto-block all four; NEVER auto-allow all four.

